<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102147670015212></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102147670015212><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=102147670015212>Multiple mobs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=102147670015212#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=12608><span id=Scholar>XanPrime Defender of Justice</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 15th 11:40 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a question for the forum that relates to a Mage soloing multiple mobs.<br><br>The problem that I run into no matter what pet I use is when the pet is fighting two or more mobs and one decides to aggro on me.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>I try using the /pet back off command, but by the time the pet decides to listen to me and attack the mob on me, the one that it was fighting hits him and takes his attention.  At this point, his poor master is getting the tar beated out of him as he faithfully solos the other mob.<br><br>I've tried the Run-At-Your-Pet but I've found that to be neigh ineffective.<br><br>So what happens is that my pet ends up soloing one or more mobs as I desperately try to nuke the one on my inbetween its poundings of me.<br><br>Any advice, Magicians?  I enjoy my soloing, but any more than one mob and I'm in serious danger.<br>&nbsp;<br>======================<br>Madrigan 35 Erudite Magician<br>Itarax 40 Iksar Shaman<br>Vetachi 18 Iksar Monk<br>Balorin 16 Halfling Rogue</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
