<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10212999664215></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10212999664215><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=10212999664215>Who is the best soloing class</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=10212999664215#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Sage>Yosa</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>112 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 13th 10:34 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wanting to expericance something new, I dicide to make a Mage.&nbsp;&nbsp;So naturally I came here to get some insight into playing this class.  While doing so I noticed a lot of post on which class is the best at soloing.  And I will admit that properly twinked almost any class can solo for a number of lvls.  <br><br>In the end there are two kinds of soloing, contact and noncontact.  An example of nocontact is kiting by a druid.  An example of contact is a Mage and pet soloing.  In general higher lvl mobs can be soloed by nocontact methoods than by contact methoods.  This is because in noncontact you don't have to kill the mob faster than it is killing you or your pet as the case may be. <br><br>The advantage of contact soloing is it can be done in many more places, and it takes less time and there is less chance of Adds. <br><br>Both Shaman and Magicians make very strong contact soloers, and I assume the same is true for Beastloards.  Druids and Necromancers are the stronges of nocontact soloers.  Wiz can be very efficent as well.  Shaman can also root dot and kite to some extent.  <br><br>All in all more important than which class is the stronges, is which class fits your play style.  Me? I like contact, I like to play relativly untwinked, and I like to loot my equipment more than i like to buy it.  For these reasions I perfer the shaman and the magician to the druid and the necromancer. <br><br>In the end you will be much stronger if the class you play fits well with what you enjoy doing.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
