oup situation where you more then liekly have good melee and possibly KEI. With how poorly pets taunt chain nuking when soloing is suicide as a general rule. (except in quick fights with an epic anyway, and how many mages even <i>have</i> that blasted thing)<br><br>&quot;If ya wanna solo as a mage you gotta know how to play your class. That means going in and taking hits for your pet occasionally, pet kiting, and chain summoning. If you know how to do these THEN you can be an extremely effective soloer.&quot;<br><br>You're talking to a mage who solo'd high blues at 55. I know these things:D<br><br>&quot;And yer forgetting AFK exp too. Show me a necro that can summon a pet and walk away for a half a day while it rips the hell out of a spawn. (talking of the epic here).&quot;<br><br>Yeah, if you wanna risk getting suspended for it.<br><br>&quot;There are classes that can do things we can't, but we can do things that other classes can't. It's called class balance. You can't point to any class and say that they're flat out the &quot;best&quot; soloer. I've done things that I know a necro woulda had a damn hard time with, and vice versa. It's all situational.&quot;<br><br>I invite you to name a mob that you can solo and an equivelently equipped/skilled necromancer can't. Or heck, even a monk who has decent stuff. And yes, it's all situational. <br><br>Now, I'm not trying to flame anyone. I'm <i>not</i> trying to say that mages suck at soloing. If done properly, mages can be pretty good. But what I <i>am</i> trying to say is that, unless you're a necromancer, shaman, or melee with NToV/Luclin boss equipment soloing is inefficient and pointless past a certain level, and really it makes no sense to say a class is or isn't good solely based on what they can or can't solo in a game that wasn't designed with soloing in mind in the first place.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun May 12 10:49:24 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
